Thanks for your work on json5!. Absolutely! My use case is very specific: I am building an animation component that accepts a `keyframes` object or string. For my convenience and skim-ability, I often prefer to use a string, like:

```jsx
<Animate
  animation={`{
    0: {
      opacity: 0.5,
    },
    0.5: {
      opacity: 0,
    },
    1: {
      opacity: 1,
    }
  }`}
  duration={500}
>
```

`Animate` takes this string and converts it to an object using json5. For number-type consistency within this `animation` string, I do not want to force devs to add quotes around the keys, it "feels" more jarring:

```jsx
<Animate
  animation={`{
    '0': {
      opacity: 0.5,
    },
    '0.5': {
      opacity: 0,
    },
    '1': {
      opacity: 1,
    }
  }`}
  duration={500}
>
```

